BEGIN_PGML
To kill bedbug eggs using heat, they must be exposed to at least [`118^{\circ}F`] for at least 90 minutes. If you only know the Celsius temperature [`C\text{,}`] then to kill the eggs means we have the inequality [`\frac{9}{5}C+32\geq118\text{.}`] You have some infested blankets that you put in a sauna for 90 minutes, but the sauna temperature is [`[$proposed_solution]^{\circ}C\text{.}`] Was this hot enough to kill the eggs?

